column168: DURING TRANSIT, VIBRATIONS CAUSED A TRANSFORMER TO ROTATE WHILE CHAINED DOW N ON A FLATBED. [THE STEEL FLOOR OF THE TRAILER (USED AS SECONDARY CONTAINM ENT IN THE EVENT OF LEAKAGE) CREATES A SLIPPERY SURFACE WHICH MAKES IT DIFF ICULT TO PREVENT MONOR ROTATION OF CARGO.] THIS ROTATION CAUSED A VALVE TO BREAK OFF AGAINST A CHAIN WHILE THE TRAILER WAS TURNING INTO THE YARD OF TH E CONSIGNEE. THE BROKEN VALVE CAUSED THE RELEASE OF OIL CONTAMINATED WITH 2 18 PPM POLYCHLORIMATED BIPHENYLS. A SMALL AMOUNT (LESS THAN 10 LBS) OF THIS OIL WAS RELEASED TO THE ENVIRONMENT (ASPHALT SURFACE). THE CONTAMINATED SU RFACES WERE DOUBLE-RINSED AND CLEANED IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE EPA'S TSCA PCB SPILL CLEAN-UP PROCEDURE (40 CFR 761 SUBPART G). CLEAN-UP WAS PERFORMED BY HAZMAT AND THE CONSIGNEE RESULTING IN ONE DRUM OF CONTAMINATED DEBRIS. THI S DRUM WAS GENERATED ON THE CONSIGNEE'S SITE AND IT REMAINED THERE, AS THE CONSIGNEE IS A LICENSED PCB FACILITY.

column168: THE VEHICLE WAS TRAVELLING WEST ON I-80 WHEN, WITH A COMBINATION OF WEATHER CONDITIONS AND DRIVER ERROR, THE TRANSPORT VEHICLE WENT OFF THE LEFT SHOULDER AND OVERTURNED, SPILLING THE CONTENTS OF FIVE (5) OF THE SIX (6) CONTAINERS BEING TRANSPORTED.  DETAILS OF THE CLEAN-UP AND CONDITIONS OF THE SITE AFTER CLEAN-UP ARE ATTACHED.  THE INCIDENT INVOLVED A RADIOACTIVE LSA SHIPMENT EN ROUT FROM QUADREX RECYCLE CENTER IN OAK RIDGE, TENNESSEE, TO U.S. ECOLOGY BURIAL SITE IN RICHLAND, WASHINGTON, VIA KINDRICK TRUCKING COMPANY.  THE LOCATION OF THE ACCIDENT WAS ON INTERSTATE 80 WEST AT MILE MARK 331.8, BETWEEN CHEYENNE AND LARAMIE.  CLEAN-UP OPERATIONS WERE PERFORM ED BY QUADREX WHICH INVOLVED THE RETRIEVAL OF SIX RADIOACTIVE LSA CONTAINER S AND THE REMOVAL OF THE RESULTANT SPILLAGE.  FIVE OF THE SIX CONTAINERS INVOLVED WERE BREACHED, LOSING APPROXIMATELY ONE-THIRD OF THEIR CONTENTS EACH.  ONE OF THE SIX CONTAINERS REMAINED INTACT WITH NO LOSS OF CONTENTS OR STRUCTURAL INTEGRITY.
